{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771326038,"nonce":"2rhcp/M4zBLDgklEmcjwtqGUHac=","title":"Discussion: role permissions for item management (Mitarbeitende)","message":"Observed that Mitarbeitende (member role) may not be able to add new items in the UI, even though the ability model grants them 'can :manage, ParentItem' scoped to their department.\n\nCurrent role hierarchy (from ability.rb):\n- guest (Gast): read-only access\n- member (Mitarbeitende): manage items, lendings, borrowers in their department\n- leader (Leitende): same as member plus user management within department\n- admin: manage everything\n\nQuestions to discuss:\n- Is the intent that Mitarbeitende should be able to create/edit items? The ability model says yes.\n- If so, is this a UI issue where the 'add item' button is hidden for non-leaders?\n- Should the permission model be revisited? What should each role be able to do?","files":null}]}